OL,6,FThe defendant, who is believed to be
OL,7,Fthe first person convicted of
OL,8,Forganising boat crossings across the
OL,9,FMediterranean from the UK, was
OL,10,Fsentenced at Southwark Crown Court on
OL,11,FTuesday to 25 years, having pleaded
OL,12,Fguilty to conspiracy to assist
OL,13,Funlawful immigration.
OL,15,FReacting to the sentence, Prime
OL,16,FMinister Sir Keir Starmer said on X:
OL,17,F"Good. I am determined to smash the
OL,18,Fsmall boat gangs behind the vile trade
OL,19,Fin people smuggling."
